It looks like you have no valid return. The error means it calls itself so many times python just gives up.
Example (good) will end after &#39;&#39;num&#39;&#39; times:

    def a(x, num):
      if num == 0:
        return x
      return a(x + 1, num - 1)

Example (bad) will never return anything else as itself:

    def a(x, num):
      if num == 0:
        return x
      return a(x + 1, num)

Assuming you mean you want it to return a string representation of the function as called:

    def a (x,y):
       *code*
       return f&quot;a({x},{y})&quot;

Alternatively if you are not able to use f-strings:

